  "prompt": "Why does Enrique Iglesias always wear a cap when performing?",
  "response": "Enrique Iglesias often wears a cap during performances for a combination of personal style, branding, and practical reasons. Here are some possible explanations:\n\n1. **Signature Look**: Over time, the cap has become part of Enrique Iglesias' signature style, making him easily recognizable to fans and adding to his unique stage persona.\n\n2. **Comfort and Practicality**: Wearing a cap can help keep hair out of his face during energetic performances, especially under stage lighting, which can cause sweating.\n\n3. **Versatility**: Caps are casual and versatile, fitting well with Enrique's music style and stage presence. They also allow him to blend fashion with functionality.\n\n4. **Branding and Consistency**: Consistently wearing a cap helps reinforce his image and makes his look memorable, which is important for an artist's branding.\n\n5. **Personal Preference**: Ultimately, it may simply be a matter of personal choice. Enrique has said in interviews that he feels more comfortable wearing a cap, and it has become a part of his identity as an artist.\n\nThe cap has become such a recognizable part of his image that it\u2019s now associated with his performances and adds to his overall appeal.",
